@startuml
participant Scheduler as "TMF915 Scheduled Sync"
participant S3 as "MinIO (S3 Backend)"
participant MLflowClient as "MLflow Tracking Server"
participant DB as "TMF915 Catalog DB"
participant API as "/aiModel API"
participant Lifecycle as "Lifecycle & Deployer"
participant MLflowCLI as "MLflow CLI"
participant Docker as "Docker Engine"

== 1. High Speed Synchronization Phase ==
Scheduler -> MLflowClient: Fetch Logged Models / Registry
MLflowClient --> Scheduler: Return metadata mapping
Scheduler -> S3: fast HEAD request (MinioClient) check artifact URIs
S3 --> Scheduler: File validation true/false
Scheduler -> DB: create AiModelSpecification (Positive/Negative Caching used)

== 2. Instantiation Request ==
API -> Lifecycle: POST /aiModel (state: RESERVED, specId: <id>)
Lifecycle -> DB: Persist AiModel (RESERVED)

== 3. Deployment & Build Caching ==
Lifecycle -> Docker: ProcessBuilder: check if image 'm-<mlflow-model-id>' exists
Docker --> Lifecycle: Returns Image status
alt Image does not exist
  Lifecycle -> MLflowCLI: mlflow models build-docker --model-uri <uri>
  MLflowCLI --> Lifecycle: Docker image built
end

== 4. Container Provisioning ==
Lifecycle -> Lifecycle: generateContainerName(AiModel.name + version limits)
Lifecycle -> Docker: docker run -d -p <port> --name <container-name> m-<mlflow-model-id>
Docker --> Lifecycle: Container Started

== 5. Response Structuring ==
Lifecycle -> DB: updateAiModelState(ACTIVE / DESIGNED)
Lifecycle --> API: Hide 'serviceSpecification', respond with 'aiModelSpecification'
@enduml
